The Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger network requires recovery of administrative satchels abandoned in the Manifest Shade Court district when the last adjudicator rotation collapsed, and the Midgaard postmaster has been tasked with coordinating the recovery effort. Each recovered satchel contains burn ledger entries that cannot be reconstructed from secondary sources. Locate one intact registrar's satchel in the administrative district and return it to the postmaster.
The registrar's heatproof satchel has been recovered and its burn ledger contents confirmed intact. The Midgaard postmaster has forwarded the recovered entries to the Southern Oasis Casualty Ledger network, closing a gap in the administrative record that predates the current adjudicator cycle. A formal recovery confirmation has been transmitted to the Ration Dispute Court for archive purposes.

